@janb84, thanks for the review.

> To consider; change title to "must find a fitting solution" in stead of "must find a good solution", but it's a very small nit.

I think "good" is just as descriptive as "fine" here although I really don't care either way about the title.

>  If you search for e.g., the target amount, you might notice that the first few tests of this set were copied from the SRD tests. In the context of the CoinGrinder pull request, the tests were also used to demonstrate how later optimizations reduce the count of attempts necessary to determine the optimal solution.

@murchandamus I see that now: https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/blob/e486597f9a57903600656fb5106858941885852f/src/wallet/test/coinselector_tests.cpp#L1379.  However, in the parlance of SRD, there is no such thing as a "good solution", only "a solution" since all solutions are random.  Since this test is adapted to CoinGrinder, I think it makes sense to strengthen the test by asserting it finds a "good" solution.

